{"turn": 11, "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"in": 2, "out": 3731, "cache_read": 19540, "cache_write": 800}, "blocks": [{"signature": "", "thinking": "", "type": "thinking"}, {"text": "# Executive Summary \u2014 Spring Glow Creative Campaign\n\n**Prepared from internal company records; all figures and claims cited to source documents.**\n\n## Campaign Overview\nThe Spring Glow Campaign (internally tracked under project code \"SGX\" \u2014 Spring Glow Campaign Execution) launched on **2025-07-15** following an internal team briefing, supporting the GlowSerum product launch into Acme Retail stores (*operations/shared_drive/ticket_1939_216.txt; operations/shared_drive/policy_0783_624.md*). It has been jointly managed by Northstar Media's Campaign Department (Creative Director Ivy Tanaka; Campaign Manager Marco Nguyen) together with the Analytics Team (*campaign/reports/status_report_0660_511.md*).\n\n## Total Spend \u2014 \u26a0\ufe0f Not fully reconciled\nThe clearest single figure on record is **$48,700 total spend allocated across all creative assets** for the Spring Glow Campaign, as of week 27 (2025-07-27), with 45% to digital, 30% to print, and 25% to in-store activations, and 68% of that budget utilized at the time of reporting (*campaign/reports/status_report_0660_511.md*, authored by Ivy Tanaka, Creative Director).\n\nHowever, this figure should be treated as a **snapshot, not a final total**:\n- A separate vendor-invoice ledger for the SGX project (*operations/shared_drive/budget_0446_702.csv*) records an additional **$109,600** in creative-related invoices between September\u2013November 2025, billed to Kangaroo Designs, NorthPac Legal, and Aurora Research Pty Ltd.\n- Internal audits explicitly state the total spend across Spring Glow creative campaigns **\"hasn't been fully aggregated\"** due to data-entry delays and overlapping project codes (*hr/archive/email_0165_770.eml* / *legal/archive/email_0165_770.eml*, Dec 2025), a concern echoed in the internal spend-tracking policy (*finance/old/policy_0615_666.md*).\n- A separate **AUD 385,000 budget** (not actual spend) was later approved for the SGX campaign's 2026 execution phase \u2014 AUD 120,000 creative production, AUD 150,000 digital media, AUD 115,000 research/analytics (*campaign/memos/memo_0778_234.md*).\n\n**Recommendation:** Treat $48,700 as the only figure formally labeled \"Total Spend\" in the record, but flag to Finance that reconciliation against the $109,600 invoice ledger and the FY2026 budget is still outstanding before reporting a final consolidated number.\n\n## Creative Concepts\nNo single document lists a formally \"approved\" concept slate. The invoice ledger for the SGX project records the following named creative concepts/taglines billed against it: *\"Echo your journey,\" \"Create with clarity,\" \"Design with purpose,\" \"Creative strategy,\" \"Step into the glow,\"* and *\"Vision beyond the screen\"* (*operations/shared_drive/budget_0446_702.csv*). Separately, a 2026 memo notes that **final concept approvals from Melbournescope Studios were due 2026-02-15**, but does not name the concepts themselves (*campaign/memos/memo_0778_234.md*).\n\n## Delivering Agencies/Teams\n- **Kangaroo Designs** \u2014 graphic design vendor; delivered visual/creative assets (*campaign/reports/status_report_0660_511.md; operations/shared_drive/budget_0446_702.csv*)\n- **Aussie Web Solutions** \u2014 digital platform integration (*campaign/reports/status_report_0660_511.md*)\n- **Dingo Consulting** \u2014 delivered the first batch of creative assets ahead of schedule during the SGX execution phase (*operations/shared_drive/status_report_0464_947.txt*)\n- **Melbournescope Studios** \u2014 named \"primary creative partner\" for the 2026 SGX phase (*campaign/memos/memo_0778_234.md*)\n- Internal oversight: Campaign Department (Creative Director Ivy Tanaka; Campaign Manager Marco Nguyen), Northstar Media Pty Ltd.\n\n## Note on Source Reliability\nMultiple documents reference \"Spring Glow\"/\"SGX\" across different dates (2025 and 2026) with inconsistent spend totals and vendor rosters. This summary presents only figures/claims explicitly stated in company records, with direct citations; it does not reconcile the conflicting totals, as no single authoritative document does so as of the latest available report (Dec 2025).", "type": "text"}]}
